      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(whatsapp): notify sender after pairing approval",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add WhatsApp approval notifications to the existing channel pairing `--notify` path by routing approval delivery through the shared outbound `sendMessage` gateway path.\n- Keep the public pairing adapter surface closed; the WhatsApp path uses the `createChatChannelPlugin` text pairing `delivery: \"outbound-message\"` mode instead of loose adapter fields.\n- Document the outbound-message pairing delivery mode in the channel plugin SDK docs.\n- Add and fix focused WhatsApp pairing coverage for notification wiring and normalization.\n\nFixes #56619.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/channels/plugins/pairing.test.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing-adapters.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/channel.pairing.test.ts src/cli/pairing-cli.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.tooling.config.ts test/scripts/plugin-prerelease-test-plan.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/whatsapp/src/channel.pairing.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/whatsapp/src/channel.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/channel.pairing.test.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing.types.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing-adapters.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing-adapters.test.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing.ts src/plugin-sdk/core.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing.test.ts`\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/whatsapp/src/channel.pairing.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Approving a WhatsApp pairing request with notification enabled now sends the shared pairing-approved message back through the OpenClaw outbound send path, so WhatsApp delivery is handled by the running gateway instead of a short-lived local helper.\n\nReal environment tested: Local full OpenClaw checkout on PR branch `codex/whatsapp-pairing-approval-notify-56619-20260618`, exercising the WhatsApp pairing adapter, plugin SDK text pairing builder, pairing CLI channel wiring, and shared pairing adapter helpers through the repository Vitest harness after the patch.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/channels/plugins/pairing.test.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing-adapters.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/channel.pairing.test.ts src/cli/pairing-cli.test.ts --reporter=dot\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.tooling.config.ts test/scripts/plugin-prerelease-test-plan.test.ts --reporter=dot\nnode_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/whatsapp/src/channel.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/channel.pairing.test.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing.types.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing-adapters.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing-adapters.test.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing.ts src/plugin-sdk/core.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing.test.ts\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal capture from the focused pairing run showed the gateway-backed notification wiring and adapter behavior passing:\n\n```text\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.cli.config.ts\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.extension-whatsapp.config.ts\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.channels.config.ts\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests       13 passed (13)\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests       2 passed (2)\n\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests       4 passed (4)\n\n[test] passed 3 Vitest shards\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The plugin SDK pairing test verifies `delivery: \"outbound-message\"` creates a `notifyApproval` closure that calls the shared outbound `sendMessage` with the approved target id, shared approval message, channel id, account id, and config. The WhatsApp test verifies the plugin exposes `notifyApproval` without loose pairing adapter fields, and the normalization test verifies WhatsApp-prefixed phone entries still normalize correctly. CLI and shared adapter tests remain green.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live WhatsApp transport session was not started in this environment; the focused plugin pairing tests exercise the changed approval notification path without external WhatsApp credentials.",
